	Everyday Health, Inc. - About Us























































Everyday Health, Inc.
operates a leading digital marketing and communications platform for healthcare companies that want to engage with consumers and healthcare professionals.








Our Business Model


Everyday Health, Inc.’s platform combines premier content from leading brands, a large and engaged audience, and extensive data and analytics expertise to provide a highly personalized content experience for our users and an efficient marketing channel for our diverse set of customers. 


We attract a large and engaged audience of consumers and healthcare professionals to our premium health content across multiple channels, including the web, mobile devices, video and social media, and utilize our data and analytics expertise to deliver highly personalized user experiences. The combination of our audience, content and proprietary data assets also creates a unique health engagement platform that we monetize through effective marketing and engagement solutions that address the varied business needs of constituencies across the health and wellness landscape.

Scroll to learn about each business unit.



Everyday Health Consumer




Over 70 MILLION consumer registrations since inception



Everyday Health’s consumer-focused properties include online content, interactive tools and applications designed to allow consumers to manage a broad array of health and wellness needs. Everyday Health, our flagship brand, is a broad-based health information portal that provides consumers with trusted and actionable health information intended to empower users to better manage their health and wellness. We also operate the digital website and mobile applications for the What to Expect brand, the leading pregnancy and parenting media resource based on the best-selling pregnancy book, What to Expect When You’re Expecting, by author Heidi Murkoff. Through What to Expect, we currently reach approximately 50% of all pregnant women in the U.S. each year.

We provide digital health marketing and communications solutions targeted to consumers. Since our inception, more than 70 million consumers have registered with us online and voluntarily provided us with valuable data, including demographic information and health-related interests. We augment our user profiles by collecting behavioral data through engagement with our properties and appending data from third-party sources. Our proprietary technology utilizes the data we collect to provide a highly-personalized experience for our consumers, including customized content, to drive better health outcomes and to connect users looking for support. We reach approximately 50 million consumers each month.
Our sales solutions enable pharmaceutical customers to drive patient volume across their product portfolio, whether orphan, specialty or mass-market, and across the product lifecycle, whether pre-launch, during the patent exclusivity period or post-patent exclusivity. CPG, OTC, and retail pharmacies can also leverage our large consumer base to communicate with relevant audiences for their products or services, by utilizing our large audience of consumers, targeting capabilities both on- and off-portfolio, and engaging content. Everyday Health Consumer solutions are delivered through multiple channels, including desktop, mobile web, and mobile phone and tablet applications, as well as video and social media.






Everyday Health Professional




Reaching over 700,000 
practicing U.S. physicians



Everyday Health Professional provides digital health marketing and communications solutions targeted to healthcare professionals. We currently reach an audience of over 700,000 practicing U.S. physicians across numerous specialty areas on our premier properties, including MedPage Today. Our highly-tailored content experiences enable healthcare professionals to stay informed, receive tools that aid in their clinical practice, make better decisions for their patients, and deliver better outcomes. Our partnerships with prominent healthcare professionals and premier medical associations allow us to provide expert commentary and perspectives on important medical developments. We also offer physicians the ability to participate in market research and satisfy continuing medical education, or CME, requirements for maintenance of licensure and maintenance of certification through engagement with our content.

Our sales solutions enable pharmaceutical customers to drive increased prescriptions across their product portfolio, whether orphan, specialty or mass-market, and across the product lifecycle, whether pre-launch, during the patent exclusivity period or post-patent exclusivity. Everyday Health Professional solutions are offered in a variety of business models and delivered through multiple channels, including desktop, mobile web, and mobile phone and tablet applications.






Healthcare Solutions




Marketing & communications solutions for hospitals &
 health insurers



Everyday Health provides robust consumer engagement, marketing and communications solutions to hospital systems and health insurers.
Our sophisticated software platform enables hospital systems to recruit new patients and physicians, retain existing patients and physicians, influence where physicians refer their patients, and control costs. Hospital systems can leverage our technology, content, and audience to better drive their growth strategies and generate profitable revenue by identifying high value customers and engaging in segmented and targeted marketing campaigns using proprietary and third-party data, such as payer distribution, medical history, health claims data, purchase history and behavioral data. We currently work with 6 of the top 10 largest health systems, including more than 350 hospitals across 30 states. To learn more about our hospital offering, visit Tea Leaves Health. 
Health insurers can also leverage our platform to recruit consumers and better manage medical conditions and daily health across areas such as nutrition, stress, physical activity, and weight loss. Our core offering for health payers is our Maternity Outcomes Management (MOM) program, which leverages our What to Expect property and connects pregnant women with their insurance carrier’s risk management programs earlier in their pregnancies, allowing payers to identify risk factors earlier and introduce meaningful interventions, if necessary, so as to ensure safer and healthier pregnancies.





Cambridge BioMarketing




The leader in strategic launch & marketing solutions for orphan &
rare disease products



Cambridge BioMarketing, a division of Everyday Health, Inc., is the leader in strategic launch and marketing solutions for orphan and rare disease products. Cambridge’s mission is to help its clients transform the lives of people with devastating diseases and the physicians who treat them. The Cambridge team uses deep clinical understanding, informed research, and strategic insight to build interactive and engaging marketing programs for their pharmaceutical and biotech customers, targeted at engaging sufferers of orphan and rare diseases which, in the U.S. are defined as diseases with fewer than 200,000 patients. To learn more, visit Cambridge BioMarketing. 




Leadership Team





Corporate Leadership








Michael  du Toit

,


,

, President



Michael is President of Everyday Health. He is responsible for managing Everyday Health’s consumer and professional businesses, including product, editorial, sales and sales development. His responsibilities also include guiding Everyday Health’s strategic direction and growth, while ensuring the company remains an innovative market leader in digital health.
With more than 30 years of experience in healthcare and consumer media and marketing, Michael is a highly-accomplished executive with deep relationships across the health and wellness industry. Michael has a proven track record of driving strong financial results, leading innovative and growing organizations and mentoring those who work with him.
Prior to joining Everyday Health, Michael was an executive at Publicis Groupe S.A. for nine years, serving most recently as Global Group President for Publicis Healthcare Communications Group, the largest healthcare communications network in the world. In this role, Michael was responsible for managing Digitas Health, Publicis Lifebrands Medicus and Medicus International. While at Publicis, Michael also served as President of Digitas Health - where he was a founding member - and Razorfish Health. Michael also spent five years at Glaxo where as Vice President of Marketing he was responsible for launching several blockbuster pharmaceutical products. He started his career at Unilever and has also worked at Grey Global Group and BBD&O.
Mr. du Toit received a B.S. in Economics and Marketing from Stellenbosch University in South Africa. 










Miki Kapoor

,


,

, President



With almost two decades of experience exclusively in healthcare – healthcare operations, finance, strategy and policy – Miki Kapoor has a notably broad perspective on the U.S. healthcare system. He currently serves as President of Everyday Health, responsible for broadening the Company’s reach into payors, providers, employers and risk-bearing entities in healthcare.Mr. Kapoor joined Everyday Health from IMS Health, where he served as Head of the Global Payor/Provider Division as well as Global Head of Strategy and Innovation. Prior to joining IMS Health, Miki was Head of North America and Senior Expert for McKinsey & Company's Advanced Healthcare Analytics unit, which provides healthcare analytic and advisory services to payors and providers. Before joining McKinsey & Company, Miki was the Global Head of Health Systems and Health Finance for President Clinton’s foundation, where he headed a division of approximately eighty highly-trained healthcare and public health professionals to design and execute cost-efficiency and access transformations in the developing world. Prior to his work at the Clinton Foundation, Miki spent seven years at Cowen & Company, a Wall Street investment bank, where he served as a M&A and corporate finance investment banker focused on healthcare services, payors and providers, biotechnology, and healthcare information technology.Miki attended graduate school at Yale University, where he earned both an MBA in Finance and an MPH in Health Policy. He is a graduate of Washington University in Saint Louis, where he earned a bachelor’s in biology. He is a Fulbright Fellow, formerly a visiting professor at two universities, and on the boards of several healthcare organizations.









Business Leadership








Maureen Franco

,


,

, CEO, Cambridge BioMarketing



Maureen is CEO of Cambridge BioMarketing. A biotechnology industry veteran with extensive product marketing and international market development experience, Maureen spent over a decade at Genzyme (now a Sanofi company) prior to joining Cambridge BioMarketing, During her tenure there, she served in multiple leadership roles across commercial development, product marketing, global brand management, and product promotions.  Maureen began her career in pharmaceutical communications and healthcare public relations.  Her work has been focused on commercializing groundbreaking therapeutics in the specialty therapeutics and rare genetic disease markets.  Maureen received a B.S. in Management and Marketing from Boston College.










Michael Rose

,


,

, EVP, General Manager, What to Expect



Michael Rose is EVP, General Manager of the What to Expect division of Ziff Davis. In this role, Michael oversees editorial, product, sales, technology, marketing and business development for the top-ranked and rated What to Expect mobile apps and the WhatToExpect.com website. Prior to Everyday Health’s acquisition by Ziff-Davis in December 2016, Michael was President of the Pregnancy & Parenting Division of Everyday Health.  From September 2012 until October 2015, Michael served as Senior Vice President of Product and General Manager for the Lifestyle division of Everyday Health.Michael has spent over 20 years building and scaling leading software-driven media and technology companies. From August 2010 until August 2012, Michael led business development, advertising sales and marketing at Sulia, a subject-based social network. From 2006 to 2010, Michael was Senior Vice President of Product at Gerson Lehrman Group, the world’s largest membership-based network for professional learning and expertise. There he transitioned the company from a pure professional services organization into a technology- and platform-enabled marketplace. From 2004 to 2006, Michael was Vice President of Council Partnerships at Gerson Lehrman Group. In this role he doubled the size of the company’s membership database, and scaled recruiting operations in Europe and Asia to provide GLG with a massive market-leading position. From 1996 to 2002, Michael held several positions at iVillage, Inc., where he was a founding member of the company’s marketing department, ran the business development group and launched its first subscription services. Prior to 1996 Michael worked in marketing at News Corporation’s first digital media company (Delphi Internet) and as well as in marketing and public relations for several leading entertainment companies.Michael received a Bachelor of Arts from the George Washington University.






















